	  _V_r_m_a_i_l provides a visual, mouse based	interface to elec-
	  tronic mail on the 630/730 terminals.	 The interface con-
	  sists	of two parts.  The host	part is	in charge of interfac-
	  ing with UUUUNNNNIIIIXXXX	to manipulate the electronic mail and provide
	  information needed to	manipulate the display on the terminal
	  screen.  The terminal	part allows the	user to	select a mes-
	  sage and to then have	some (mostly user defined) function
	  performed on that message.

	  Other	programs such as _v_i_e_w_m_a_i_l(_1) (from which _v_r_m_a_i_l	was
	  derived) and _x_v_i_s_m_a_i_l(_1) only	provide	a notification facil-
	  ity.	_V_r_m_a_i_l provides	the ability to interact	with the mail
	  messages.  Messages can be read, replied to, forwarded and
	  other	such actions.

	  The user can define what happens to messages by creating a
	  menu and assigning a particular operation to each menu item.
	  A default menu and the associated set	of operations is pro-
	  vided	as a base.  The	user can expand	the menu and associ-
	  ated operations as desired.

