     CCCCAAAAVVVVEEEEAAAATTTTSSSS
	  It is	possible that addresses	which contain only login names
	  without a host specification might be	magically translated
	  via the post lookup mechanism	to a different person than the
	  original recepient.  I.e.  if	the address is simply 'res'
	  and there is such a person on	the local machine and a	single
	  person exists	in post	with this surname, the mail will go to
	  the address specified	in post	for this person, not to	the
	  local	user 'res'.

	  Some race conditions when accessing the same mail box	simul-
	  taneously from different _v_r_m_a_i_l instances are	not guarded
	  against.  Beware that	due to the randomness of CPU schedul-
	  ing you might	not get	what you thought you would when
	  attempting this.

	  The %%%%ddddkkkkssssrrrrvvvv mechanism is only supported on some versions of
	  _v_r_m_a_i_l and then only if there	is a datakit service



